baseline.comment:
85% of adults and children with HIV known to be on treatment 12 months after initiation of antiretroviral therapy;
1201 eligible adults and children currently receiving antiretroviral therapy;
47,4% HIV-positive TB patients who are started on or continue
previously initiated antiretroviral therapy, during TB treatment,
among all HIV-positive TB patients registered during the
reporting period (number and percentage)

target.comment:
90% of adults and children with HIV known to be on treatment 12 months after initiation of antiretroviral therapy;
2461 eligible adults and children currently receiving antiretroviral therapy;
50% HIV-positive TB patients who are started on or continue previously initiated antiretroviral therapy, during TB treatment,
among all HIV-positive TB patients registered during the reporting period (number and percentage)

actual.comment:
